  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today. By now the keyboard should feel less like a tool and more like breathing. The work is to keep that ease at speed - one even tempo, three plain words, no strain."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word without forcing it. If the ease slips, count quietly: one, two, three, four."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "metronome",
      "title": "Even hands",
      "text": "Fluency is not effort; it is an even pace that has stopped asking for your attention. Hold one gap between keystrokes and let the hands run themselves. The smoother the rhythm, the faster it carries."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "keyboard",
      "baseReps": 5,
      "keys": ["k", "e", "y", "b", "o", "a", "r", "d"],
      "target": "keyboard keyboard keyboard keyboard keyboard",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: keyboard",
      "hint": "Repeat at one tempo: keyboard - keyboard - keyboard. Hold the gaps equal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "walking",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["w", "a", "l", "k", "i", "n", "g"],
      "target": "walking walking walking walking",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: walking",
      "hint": "Repeat steadily, no jerks: walking - walking - walking."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "friend",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["f", "r", "i", "e", "n", "d"],
      "target": "friend friend friend friend",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: friend",
      "hint": "Repeat evenly: friend - friend - friend. Do not speed up at the end."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Let the hand take each word whole and let your mind sit a step ahead of it. Even repetition is how a skill becomes second nature - the kind that simply moves with you while you think about the words, not the keys."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Loosen your shoulders and wrists, picture the metronome, and let rhythm do the work. Ease, held steady, is speed.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
